                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320517-247-off1428 t18320517-247-crimeloc1431"></join> - I did not feel my handkerchief taken, but missed it as I came out of a public-house; the prisoner was taken in five minutes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320517-247-person1842">
                  THOMAS 
                  CADE
               <interp inst="t18320517-247-person1842" type="surname" value="CADE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320517-247-person1842" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320517-247-person1842" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner and a little boy standing at the top of Milton-street - they went behind the prosecutor, and I saw the little boy take his hand from the prosecutor's pocket; they walked away up Fore-street - the prisoner was standing behind the little one; I am sure of his person - the boy ran away when he saw the prisoner was taken.</p>
               <p>THOMAS NORWOOD. I was in Fore-street, and saw a boy take a handkerchief out of the prosecutor's pocket and give it to the prisoner, who stood just behind him; he was secured, and the handkerchief found.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320517-247-person1843">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BRAND
               <interp inst="t18320517-247-person1843" type="surname" value="BRAND"></interp>
